IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO INCREASE ACCESS TO AFFORDABLE HIGH QUALITY HEALTH CARE FOR THE WHOLE FAMILY.
IRS990.MissionDesc: THE CENTER'S MISSION IS TO INCREASE ACCESS TO HIGH QUALITY COMPREHENSIVE AND PREVENTATIVE HEALTH CARE SERVICES THAT ARE CULTURALLY SENSITIVE IN ORDER TO IMPROVE THE HEALTH STATUS OF THE UNDERSERVED AND VULNERABLE RESIDENTS OF THE COMMUNITY.
IRS990.Desc: MEDICAL CARE: THE CENTER MEDICAL CARE THAT IS CULTURALLY SENSITIVE IN ORDER TO IMPROVE THE HEALTH STATUS OF THE UNDERSERVED AND VULNERABLE RESIDENTS OF PRINCE WILLIAM COUNTY AND THE CITIES OF MANASSAS AND MANASSAS PARK. THE CENTER PROGRAMS ARE DESIGNED TO INCREASE ACCESS TO HIGH QUALITY, COMPREHENSIVE AND PREVENTIVE HEALTH CARE. THIS PROGRAM HAD 26,760 VISITS INVOLVING 9,320 PATIENTS DURING THE FISCAL YEAR.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: OB-GYN CARE: THE CENTER PROVIDES OB-GYN CARE THAT IS CULTURALLY SENSITIVE IN ORDER TO IMPROVE THE HEALTH STATUS OF THE UNDERSERVED AND VULNERABLE RESIDENTS OF PRINCE WILLIAM COUNTY AND THE CITIES OF MANASSAS AND MANASSAS PARK. THIS PROGRAM HAD 14,220 VISITS INVOLVING 2,070 PATIENTS DURING THE FISCAL YEAR.

ProgSrvcAccomActyOtherGrp.Desc: BEHAVIORAL HEALTH - THE CENTER PROVIDES BEHAVIORAL HEALTH CARE THAT IS CULTURALLY SENSITIVE IN ORDER TO IMPROVE THE HEALTH STATUS OF THE UNDERSERVED AND VULNERABLE RESIDENTS OF PRINCE WILLIAM COUNTY AND THE CITIES OF MANASSAS AND MANASSAS PARK. SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD ISSUED A DISCRETIONARY BONUS TO THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR; THE PROCESS IS A CONFIDENTIAL MEETING BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS WHERE THE MATTER IS RAISED FOR CONSIDERATION AND, IF DEEMED WARRANTED, AN AMOUNT IS CONSIDERED, IF APPROVED, THEN THE BONUS IS ISSUED.
THE NUMBER IN COLUMN B REPRESENTS THE NUMBER OF CONTRIBUTORS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 1
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE SHALL CONSIST OF THE OFFICERS OF THE BOARD AND THE CHAIRMAN OF STANDING COMMITTEES. THE COMMITTEE SHALL HAVE THE POWERS OF THE GOVERNING BOARD WHEN IT IS NOT IN SESSION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR, DIRECTOR OF FINANCE, AND ACCOUNTING MANAGER PERFORM AN INITIAL REVIEW OF THE DRAFT 990. THE RETURN IS THEN PROVIDED TO THE FINANCE COMMITTEE AND BOARD OF DIRECTORS FOR REVIEW PRIOR TO FILING WITH THE IRS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: BOARD DIRECTORS, OFFICERS, AND KEY EMPLOYEES COMPLETE A DISCLOSURES FORM ANNUALLY. INDIVIDUALS WITH POTENTIAL OR ACTUAL CONFLICTS ARE EXPECTED TO REPORT ANY INFORMATION PERTINENT TO THE CONFLICT. FAMILY AND BUSINESS RELATIONSHIPS RE EXPRESSLY STATED IN THE DISCLOSURES AS BEING SOURCES OF POTENTIAL CONFLICTS. BOARD DIRECTORS MAKE THEIR DISCLOSURES TO THE COMPLIANCE OFFICER, WHILE THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR DISCLOSES ANY POTENTIAL CONFLICTS TO THE BOARD. DIRECTORS WITH A CONFLICT MAY SPEAK TO THE BOARD ON THE CONFLICT, BUT MUST LEAVE THE MEETING DURING ANY DISCUSSION OR VOTE ON WHETHER THE CONFLCT EXISTS. IF IT IS DETERMINED THAT A CONFLICT EXISTS, THE INTERESTED DIRECTOR MUST RECUSE HIMSELF OR HERSELF FROM ANY DISCUSSION OF, OR VOTING ON, THE ARRANGEMENT THAT INVOLVES THE CONFLICT.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD SETS POSITION PAY RANGES AND REVIEWS AND APPROVES THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR'S COMPENSATION AND BENEFITS. THE BOARD COMPENSATION RANGES ARE BASED ON A SALARY SURVEY OF SIMILAR ORGANIZATIONS. THE SALARY SURVEY AND BOARD DECISIONS ARE DOCUMENTED IN BOARD MINUTES. A COMPREHENSIVE REVIEW OF KEY EMPLOYEE COMPENSATION WAS LAST PERFORMED IN 2016. THE BOARD REVIEWED THE SALARY SURVEY COMPLETED BY THE NATIONAL ASSOCIATION OF COMMUNITY HEALTH CENTERS AND A FOLLOW-UP SURVEY OF VIRGINIA HEALTH CENTERS, WHICH WAS CONDUCTED BY THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR AND DIRECTOR OF HUMAN RESOURCES FROM APRIL 2016 TO SEPTEMBER 2016, THIS SURVEY WAS PRESENTED TO THE BOARD FOR REVIEW IN NOVEMBER 2016. AS A RESULT, THE BOARD APPROVED ADJUSTING KEY EMPLOYEE ANNUAL SALARIES TO ALIGN MORE FULLY WITH THE SURVEYS PRESENTED TO IT FOR CONSIDERATION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST.
